<div class="container py-5">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <i class="bi bi-shield-lock-fill display-3 text-primary"></i>
        <h1 class="mt-3">About Secure Sequentier</h1>
        <p class="lead text-muted">A web-based file signing and verification platform</p>
    </div>

    <!-- What It Does -->
    <div class="row justify-content-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-4 p-4">
                <h4><i class="bi bi-question-circle me-2 text-primary"></i>What is Secure Sequentier?</h4>
                <p>
                    Secure Sequentier is a web-based application for <strong>digitally signing</strong>,
                    <strong>hashing</strong>, and <strong>verifying</strong> files using industry-standard
                    cryptographic algorithms. It processes files through configurable subsystem applications
                    that generate signatures, hashes, and detailed reports.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    Built with <strong>ASP.NET Core</strong> on the backend and a modern MVC frontend,
                    the application supports batch processing with real-time status updates via <strong>SignalR</strong>,
                    automatic retry logic, configurable timeouts, and downloadable output packages.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- How It Works (Architecture) -->
    <div class="row justify-content-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <h3 class="text-center mb-4">
                <i class="bi bi-diagram-3 me-2"></i>How It Works
            </h3>

            <div class="architecture-step">
                <div class="step-number bg-primary text-white">1</div>
                <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 p-3">
                    <h6 class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-upload text-primary me-2"></i>File Upload</h6>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                        User uploads one or more files through the web interface. Files are sent to the backend
                        API and stored in a <strong>watch directory</strong> organized by user and target app.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="architecture-step">
                <div class="step-number bg-warning text-dark">2</div>
                <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 p-3">
                    <h6 class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-collection text-warning me-2"></i>Queue & Orchestration</h6>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                        The <strong>Orchestrator Background Service</strong> monitors the queue. When a job is pending,
                        it dequeues it, spawns the configured subsystem executable, and passes input/output paths as arguments.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="architecture-step">
                <div class="step-number bg-info text-white">3</div>
                <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 p-3">
                    <h6 class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-cpu text-info me-2"></i>Subsystem Processing</h6>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                        The signer apps (<strong>SignerApp</strong> or <strong>AdvancedSignerApp</strong>) read
                        the input file, compute cryptographic hashes (SHA-256, SHA-512, MD5), and generate:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-muted small mb-0 mt-1">
                        <li><strong>Signature file</strong> (.sig.json) — structured signature with algorithm details</li>
                        <li><strong>Hash file</strong> (.hash.txt) — plain-text hash values</li>
                        <li><strong>Signed copy</strong> — the original file with appended hash marker</li>
                        <li><strong>Report</strong> (.report.txt) — detailed processing report with timestamps</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="architecture-step">
                <div class="step-number bg-success text-white">4</div>
                <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 p-3">
                    <h6 class="mb-1"><i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success me-2"></i>Results & Download</h6>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                        Once processing completes, results are stored in the <strong>processed directory</strong>.
                        Users can view real-time status, download all outputs as a ZIP, or view a signature certificate.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Algorithms -->
    <div class="row justify-content-center mb-5">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <h3 class="text-center mb-4">
                <i class="bi bi-lock me-2"></i>Algorithms Used
            </h3>
            <div class="row g-3">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 text-center p-3 h-100">
                        <h5 class="text-primary">SHA-256</h5>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                            256-bit hash from the SHA-2 family. Used in TLS, SSL, Bitcoin, and digital signatures.
                            Produces a 64-character hex string.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 text-center p-3 h-100">
                        <h5 class="text-success">SHA-512</h5>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                            512-bit hash offering higher security. Produces a 128-character hex string.
                            Often used for password hashing and integrity verification.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-3 text-center p-3 h-100">
                        <h5 class="text-warning">MD5</h5>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-0">
                            128-bit hash for quick checksums. Produces a 32-character hex string.
                            Not recommended for security, but widely used for file integrity checks.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

